text: Tatia Gabunia (born 7 July 2000) is a Georgian footballer who plays as a goalkeeper and has appeared for the Georgia women's national team. ==Career== Gabunia has been capped for the Georgia national team, appearing for the team during the UEFA Women's Euro 2021 qualifying cycle. ==References== ==External links== * * * Category:2000 births Category:Living people Category:Women's footballers from Georgia (country) Category:Women's association football goalkeepers Category:Georgia (country) women's international footballers
